{
  "openapi": "3.0.0",
  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "https://aq.elagy.com/api/v1",
      "description": "Production environment"
    },
    {
      "url": "https://training.aq.elagy.com/api/v1",
      "description": "Training environment for onboarding new users"
    },
    {
      "url": "https://qa.aq.elagy.com/api/v1",
      "description": "QA environment"
    }
  ],
  "info": {
    "title": "AccuQuote AgentCloud REST API",
    "description": "REST API for third-party access to the AccuQuote AgentCloud platform.\n\nThe key words \"MUST\", \"MUST NOT\", \"REQUIRED\", \"SHALL\", \"SHALL NOT\", \n\"SHOULD\", \"SHOULD NOT\", \"RECOMMENDED\", \"NOT RECOMMENDED\", \"MAY\", and \n\"OPTIONAL\" in this document are to be interpreted as described in \nBCP 14 [RFC2119] [RFC8174] when, and only when, they appear in all capitals,\nas shown here.\n\n## Authentication\nThe API authenticates requests using HTTP basic authentication as described \nin [RFC 7617](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7617). Primarily, this means \nthat each request MUST include an `Authorization` header with the value \n`Basic <token>`, where `<token>` is the string `<username>:<password>`\nencoded in base 64. \n\nBecause basic authentication credentials are not encrypted, and because the \ndata may contain sensitive information, the request MUST be made over HTTPS \nusing TLS version 1.2 or higher.\n\nHTTP basic authentication is intended for server-to-server communication and \nMUST NOT be used from the client side, where end users and malicious parties \ncould potentially gain access to the unencrypted credentials.\n\n## Request Format\nEach action or resource in the API is associated with an endpoint and an \nHTTP method. Each of these defines a specific request format that MUST be \nused when making requests to the API. In general, requests with bodies \n(e.g. `POST` or `PUT`) MUST have the content type `application/json` and \nMUST have a body consisting of a single JSON value (typically an object or \narray, as defined by the specification here).\n\nRequest URIs are typically of the form `https://aq.elagy.com/api/v1/<resource>`, \nwhere `<resource>` is the path to the specific resource or action being \nrequested.\n\n### Validation\nThe following are some common requirements for individual fields in the API. \nThe requirements MUST be satisfied for a request to validate successfully.\n\n- \"MUST NOT be empty.\" The value of the field MUST NOT be an empty value, \ne.g. an empty string or array. If the field is required, then the key MUST \nbe present in the body, and the value MUST NOT be empty. If the field is \noptional, then the key MAY be omitted; however, if it is present, the value \nMUST NOT be empty.\n- \"Optional.\" This field MAY be omitted. If the field is present, the value \nMUST satisfy all other requirements. If omitted, other requirements do not \napply.\n- \"Required for [source] leads.\" Certain additional fields MAY be required \nif the lead comes from a particular source, e.g. Homebridge. In those cases, \nthe field SHALL be marked \"Required for [source] leads,\" where \"[source]\" \nwill be replaced with the name of the source for which the field is \nrequired. For leads from other sources, the field MAY be omitted.\n- \"Valid IPv4 or IPv6 address.\" If present, the field MUST be a string whose \ncontents are a valid Internet Protocol version 4 or 6 address. IPv4 is \ndefined in [RFC 791](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc791), and IPv6 is\ndefined in [RFC 8200](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc791). \n- \"Valid email address.\" If present, the field MUST contain exactly one `@` \nsymbol, with at least one character on each side.\n- \"Valid phone number.\" The number MUST be valid under the North American \nNumbering Plan (NANP). The first digit of the area code MUST NOT contain 0 \nor 1. The first digit of the prefix MUST NOT contain 0 or 1. The area code \nand prefix MUST NOT match the pattern `[2-9]11`. See \n[Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_American_Numbering_Plan#Modern_plan)\nfor a detailed explanation of the NANP.\n",
    "version": "1.0.1",
    "contact": {
      "email": "support@jaroop.com"
    },
    "x-jentic-source-url": "https://api.swaggerhub.com/apis/jaroop/agentcloud-rest-api/1.0.1/swagger.json"
  },
  "tags": [
    {
      "name": "Leads"
    },
    {
      "name": "Opportunities"
    },
    {
      "name": "Emails"
    },
    {
      "name": "Agents"
    },
    {
      "name": "Contacts"
    },
    {
      "name": "Medicare"
    }
  ],
  "paths": {
    "/leads": {
      "post": {
        "summary": "Creates a new lead",
        "tags": [
          "Leads"
        ],
        "operationId": "createLead",
        "responses": {
          "201": {
            "description": "Lead successfully created",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/LeadCreateResponse"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "A failed response typically indicating that the data was not valid\nin some way. For example, the JSON body may be malformed, the data\nmay be invalid (e.g. an unsupported product type), or the lead may\nhave failed the TCPA audit.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "Indicates that the user was not authorized to perform the requested\naction. Typically, this means the client lacks permission to create\nleads or that the campaign is not linked to the credentials used to\nmake the request.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        },
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/LeadCreateRequest"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/leads/{leadId}": {
      "put": {
        "summary": "Updates a lead",
        "tags": [
          "Leads"
        ],
        "operationId": "updateLead",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "leadId",
            "in": "path",
            "description": "The AgentCloud ID of the lead that is being updated.",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Lead successfully updated",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/LeadUpdateResponse"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "A failed response typically indicating that the data was not valid\nin some way. For example, the JSON body may be malformed, the data\nmay be invalid (e.g. an unsupported product type), or the lead may\nhave failed the TCPA audit.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "Indicates that the user was not authorized to perform the requested\naction. Typically, this means the client lacks permission to create\nleads or that the campaign is not linked to the credentials used to\nmake the request.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "The lead with the given ID could not be found.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "410": {
            "description": "Per RFC 7231, HTTP 410 (Gone) \"indicates that access to the target \nresource is no longer available at the origin server and that this \ncondition is likely to be permanent.\" The server SHALL return this \nstatus code when the client attempts to update a lead that is no \nlonger able to be updated.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        },
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/LeadUpdateRequest"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/emails/do-not-contact": {
      "post": {
        "summary": "Adds email addresses to the do-not-contact list.",
        "tags": [
          "Emails"
        ],
        "operationId": "unsubscribeEmails",
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Emails successfully unsubscribed",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/EmailDoNotContactResponse"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "A failed response, typically indicating an invalid payload. Remember \nthat at least one of the `emails` and `leads` fields in the request \nMUST be present. \n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "Indicates that one or more IDs in the request did not match any\nknown leads.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        },
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/EmailDoNotContactRequest"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/agents/available": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "Gets the number of agents available to field calls, filtered by the \ngiven parameters.\n",
        "tags": [
          "Agents"
        ],
        "operationId": "getAvailableAgents",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "state",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "A two-letter USPS state code",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "minLength": 2,
              "maxLength": 2
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "campaignTag",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "An identifier provided that will narrow the count of agents to \nspecific campaigns.\n",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "A success response containing the number of agents available \nmatching the query.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/AvailableAgents"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "A failed response, typically indicating that parameters were\nmissing or malformed.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "429": {
            "description": "Indicates that too many requests were sent to this endpoint \nrecently.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/opportunities/match": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "Gets a list of opportunities matching a set of filter parameters",
        "description": "This endpoint attempts to return limited data from opportunities\nmatching the set of filters. It is not intended to be a general search\nendpoint. Rather, the goal is to provide a way to identify the ID\nof an opportunity based on exact, case-insensitive matches on a \nlimited number of fields. While all query string parameters are \noptional, at least one must be provided\n",
        "tags": [
          "Opportunities"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "medicareBeneficiaryId",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "lastName",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Last name of one of the insured",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "dob",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Date of birth of one of the insured",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "zip",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "ZIP code of one of the insured",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "planId",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Medicare plan ID (not the AgentCloud ID)",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "partAEffectiveDate",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "When the insured was enrolled in Medicare Part A. Must be an \nISO 8601-compatible date.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "date"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "partBEffectiveDate",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "When the insured was enrolled in Medicare Part A. Must be an \nISO 8601-compatible date.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "date"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "email",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Email address of the insured",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "email"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "phone",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Phone number of the insured",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "phone"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "A success response containing the matching opportunities.\nThis response does not indicate that any matching opportunities\nwere found. It simply means that the request was executed without\nerrors. Check the request body to determine if any opportunities\nwere returned.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/MatchingOpportunities"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "A failed response, typically indicating that parameters were\nmissing or malformed.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/opportunities/{opportunityId}": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "Gets information about an opportunity",
        "description": "The opportunity model is the central model to which most data in the \nsales process is attached. The actual opportunity object itself has\nrelatively little data. Rather, most of the fields are IDs referencing\nother objects, which in most cases contain the actually useful \ninformation. Those IDs can be used to retrieve the data from other\nendpoints. For example, the insured, owner, payor, authorized user,\nand power of attorney IDs are all contact IDs, so the contact \ninformation for, e.g. the owner of the opportunity can be retrieved\nfrom `/contacts/{ownerId}`. In some cases, shortcut endpoints like\n`/opportunities/{opportunityId}/owner` are also available to reduce\nthe number of roundtrips required when you know the specific data you\nwant to request.\n",
        "tags": [
          "Opportunities"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "opportunityId",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "description": "The AgentCloud ID of the opportunity to retrieve",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Returns the requested opportunity.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Opportunity"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "A failed response, typically indicating that the request data was\nmalformed or invalid.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "The client lacks permission to access this resource.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "The given ID does not match any known opportunities.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        }
      },
      "put": {
        "summary": "Updates an opportunity",
        "description": "Because the opportunity model itself is mostly just a collection of IDs,\nthe only field that can currently be updated through this endpoint is\nthe status. To update fields on child objects, e.g. contacts or \npolicies, call the appropriate endpoints for those resources.\n",
        "tags": [
          "Opportunities"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "opportunityId",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "description": "The AgentCloud ID of the opportunity to update",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Opportunity"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Indicates that the update was successful",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Opportunity"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "A failed response, typically indicating that the request data was\nmalformed or invalid or that the status transition is not allowed.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "The client lacks permission to access this resource.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "The given ID does not match any known opportunities.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/opportunities/{opportunityId}/medicare": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "Retrieves Medicare and policy information for an opportunity",
        "description": "If the opportunity has the Medicare product type, this endpoint returns\nall Medicare and policy information for the opportunity. All other\nproduct types return an error, as they do not have Medicare data.\n",
        "tags": [
          "Opportunities",
          "Medicare"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "opportunityId",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "description": "The AgentCloud ID of the opportunity whose data is being retrieved.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Returns all Medicare-related data for the opportunity.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/OpportunityMedicare"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "A failed response, typically indicating that the request data was\nmalformed or invalid, e.g. the opportunity is not for Medicare.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "The client lacks permission to access this resource.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "The given ID does not match any known opportunities.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        }
      },
      "put": {
        "summary": "Updates Medicare and policy information for an opportunity",
        "description": "If the opportunity has the Medicare product type, this endpoint will \nall Medicare and policy information for the opportunity. All other\nproduct types return an error, as they do not have Medicare data.\n\nUse this endpoint with caution. When a contact is updated through this\nendpoint, all eligible fields will be overwritten with the data \nincluded in the request. Fields that are null or omitted will be\noverwritten with a null value, and it may not be possible to recover the \noriginal value. It is recommended that you pull the latest data \nbefore updating if you don't want to accidentally overwrite something.\n",
        "tags": [
          "Opportunities",
          "Medicare"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "opportunityId",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "description": "The AgentCloud ID of the opportunity whose data is being updated.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/OpportunityMedicare"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Returns the updated Medicare and policy data for the opportunity.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/OpportunityMedicare"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "A failed response, typically indicating that the request data was\nmalformed or invalid, e.g. the opportunity is not for Medicare.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "The client lacks permission to access this resource.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "The given ID does not match any known opportunities.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/opportunities/{opportunityId}/medicare/doctors": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "Gets all doctors listed for a Medicare patient's opportunity",
        "tags": [
          "Opportunities",
          "Medicare"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "opportunityId",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "description": "The AgentCloud ID of a Medicare opportunity",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Successfully retrieved the doctors for an opportunity. Note that \nthe array may be empty even though the request was successful.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "array",
                  "items": {
                    "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Doctor"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "The client lacks permission to access this resource.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "The given ID does not match any known opportunities.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError"
          }
        }
      },
      "post": {
        "summary": "Updates a Medicare opportunity's doctors",
        "description": "This endpoint performs an upsert operation to associate doctors\nwith a Medicare opportunity. The doctor's NPI is used to dedupe\ndoctors on a per-opportunity basis (in other words, the same NPI\nmay only be associated with one doctor per opportunity). If the\nNPI matches an existing doctor for this opportunity, then the \ndoctor's data is updated to match the request. If the NPI does\nnot match any doctors for this opportunity, a new doctor is created\nwith the data in the request.\n",
        "tags": [
          "Opportunities",
          "Medicare"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "opportunityId",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "description": "The AgentCloud ID of a Medicare opportunity",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "array",
                "minLength": 1,
                "items": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Doctor"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Returns the complete list of ALL doctors associated with this\nopportunity, including doctors that were not part of the original\nrequest.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
